obvious.prefuse.data
Class PrefuseObviousNetwork

java.lang.Object
  obvious.prefuse.data.PrefuseObviousNetwork
All Implemented Interfaces:
obvious.data.Data, obvious.data.Graph<obvious.data.Node,obvious.data.Edge>, obvious.data.Network, obvious.util.Adaptable
Direct Known Subclasses:
PrefuseObviousForest, PrefuseObviousTree
public class PrefuseObviousNetwork
extends java.lang.Object
implements obvious.data.Network

/** Implementation of an Obvious Network based on Prefuse toolkit. It should be noted that this implementation supports oriented graphs but does not support graph containing both directed and undirected edges. Prefuse to describe graphs uses 3 columns to describe: nodes Id, source and target nodes for edges. If not specified in the constructor default columns will be used to handle this task. It should be noted that if custom columns are used their type should be int and not Integer due to prefuse constraints.

Author:
Pierre-Luc Hemery
See Also:
Network

beginEdit

public void beginEdit(int col)
               throws obvious.ObviousException
Indicates the beginning of a column edit.

This function could be used to create a context when a large number of modifications happens to a same column to avoid time wasting with plenty of notifications. In this context, TableListeners could ignore notifications if wanted.

getEdgeType

Indicates if the graph is made of directed edges. In Prefuse graph, all edges follow the same "directed" attributes. There is no distinction between edges in a prefuse graph so in this implementation.
